In the last episode, Locky Qi and the others reviewed the surveillance footage from the time of the incident.

21
00:01:11,000 --> 00:01:13,980
Jingjing found the invitation letter for the Beautiful Dog Contest.

22
00:01:14,000 --> 00:01:16,980
At the competition registration desk, the organizer Mr. Hao.

23
00:01:17,000 --> 00:01:19,980
It raised Locky Qi's suspicion.

24
00:01:22,000 --> 00:01:23,980
Blood of the Ugly Dog

25
00:01:25,000 --> 00:01:26,980
No need!

26
00:01:29,000 --> 00:01:31,920
Now, one final question.

27
00:01:29,000 --> 00:01:35,920
When we came yesterday, we only mentioned the dog's and the owner's names.

28
00:01:29,000 --> 00:01:38,920
And every day you have to deal with so much data, you yourself said you can barely remember the numbering system.

29
00:01:39,000 --> 00:01:42,920
You yourself said you can barely remember the numbering system.

30
00:01:43,760 --> 00:01:46,200
So, last time, how were you able to pull the right file from the cabinet all by yourself in such a short time?

31
00:01:46,760 --> 00:01:51,200
Why can you pull the right file from the cabinet all by yourself in no time flat?

32
00:01:53,659 --> 00:01:56,200
Because...

33
00:02:05,200 --> 00:02:08,680
This dog looks exactly like the one my wife used to have.

34
00:02:08,680 --> 00:02:15,480
My wife died in a car accident two years ago.

35
00:02:15,480 --> 00:02:17,939
That dog went missing too.

36
00:02:17,939 --> 00:02:21,860
So sometimes I always dig up info on that little dog.

37
00:02:21,860 --> 00:02:26,460
Looking at this photo, it's like my wife is still alive.

38
00:02:26,460 --> 00:02:30,620
So you kidnapped the puppy.

39
00:02:30,620 --> 00:02:31,480
What? Hehehe...

40
00:02:38,480 --> 00:02:39,880
Sorry.

41
00:02:39,880 --> 00:02:43,320
I'm not gonna kidnap any animals.

42
00:02:43,320 --> 00:02:46,060
My wife loves little animals the most.

43
00:02:46,060 --> 00:02:48,360
Especially the puppy.

44
00:02:48,360 --> 00:02:51,220
If I really kidnapped it

45
00:02:51,219 --> 00:02:55,379
How could I ever face my late wife then?

46
00:02:55,379 --> 00:02:56,939
Is that your son?

47
00:02:56,939 --> 00:02:58,879
Yeah, his name's Johnny Hao.

48
00:02:58,879 --> 00:03:00,740
Where is he now?

49
00:03:00,740 --> 00:03:04,120
He's a vet at an animal clinic.

50
00:03:04,120 --> 00:03:05,520
Lives a bit far away

51
00:03:05,520 --> 00:03:07,539
Does he know this little dog?

52
00:03:07,539 --> 00:03:08,139
Yes.

53
00:03:08,139 --> 00:03:11,300
He came by almost every day recently to help.

54
00:03:11,300 --> 00:03:14,300
I even showed him this dog's file on purpose.

55
00:03:14,300 --> 00:03:18,120
He said it really looked just like his mother's dog.

56
00:03:18,120 --> 00:03:20,919
But lately, he hasn't shown up for days.

57
00:03:20,920 --> 00:03:23,360
I can't reach him by phone either.

58
00:03:23,360 --> 00:03:26,100
Are you suspecting...?

59
00:03:26,100 --> 00:03:26,500
No.

60
00:03:26,500 --> 00:03:27,740
Without evidence,

61
00:03:27,740 --> 00:03:29,340
we're just guessing for now.

62
00:03:29,340 --> 00:03:30,140
No.

63
00:03:30,140 --> 00:03:31,560
That's absolutely impossible.

64
00:03:31,560 --> 00:03:34,880
He treats animals like family.

65
00:03:34,880 --> 00:03:37,160
Why else would he become a vet?

66
00:03:37,160 --> 00:03:39,080
This is a total waste of time.

67
00:03:39,080 --> 00:03:40,040
You don't believe me?

68
00:03:40,040 --> 00:03:41,500
I'll call him again.

69
00:03:41,500 --> 00:03:42,220
No need.

70
00:03:42,220 --> 00:03:44,580
I completely understand how you feel.

71
00:03:44,580 --> 00:03:45,820
We just want to find him

72
00:03:45,820 --> 00:03:47,360
to discuss the details of the case.

73
00:03:47,360 --> 00:03:49,360
If your son isn't the culprit,

74
00:03:49,360 --> 00:03:52,220
I'm sure you'd want us to get to the truth too.

75
00:03:52,220 --> 00:03:55,340
Alright then.

76
00:03:55,340 --> 00:03:58,920
He rented a single-story house in the suburbs himself

77
00:03:58,920 --> 00:04:03,160
At No. 69, Songyu Street, Suwu Ridge

78
00:04:03,160 --> 00:04:05,800
Thank you for your cooperation

79
00:04:05,800 --> 00:04:07,020
Let's go

80
00:04:12,020 --> 00:04:13,540
Hello? Inspector Sima?

81
00:04:13,540 --> 00:04:15,700
I have an important suspect

82
00:04:15,700 --> 00:04:18,920
Please meet me at Suwu Ridge immediately

83
00:04:19,360 --> 00:04:38,620
Hawxing

84
00:04:38,620 --> 00:04:39,199
Uncle!

85
00:04:39,199 --> 00:04:40,540
Can't let him get away!

86
00:04:40,540 --> 00:04:42,580
Not bad at all

87
00:04:42,580 --> 00:04:43,560
Without even notifying him

88
00:04:43,560 --> 00:04:45,800
He still managed to find this place so fast

89
00:04:45,800 --> 00:04:46,540
Quick, quick, quick, quick, quick

90
00:04:46,540 --> 00:04:48,540
Whoa

91
00:04:52,540 --> 00:04:56,540
A giant super-powered combo alarm clock

92
00:04:56,540 --> 00:04:58,540
So annoying, so annoying

93
00:04:58,540 --> 00:05:01,540
Why is it so lively today?

94
00:05:22,540 --> 00:05:25,040
The dog, where is it?

95
00:05:25,040 --> 00:05:30,840
Are you Hao Qiangni?

96
00:05:30,840 --> 00:05:32,900
That's me

97
00:05:32,900 --> 00:05:35,580
Yes, I'm the one who kidnapped the dog

98
00:05:35,580 --> 00:05:36,340
Why?

99
00:05:36,340 --> 00:05:37,939
Once

100
00:05:37,939 --> 00:05:41,280
I saw this dog's file from my dad

101
00:05:41,280 --> 00:05:44,040
It just reminded me of the dog my mom used to keep

102
00:05:44,040 --> 00:05:47,280
But my mom has passed away

103
00:05:47,280 --> 00:05:50,240
And the little dog that stayed with her day and night was gone too

104
00:05:50,240 --> 00:05:53,200
I miss my mom so much

105
00:05:53,200 --> 00:05:55,560
I don't know why

106
00:05:55,560 --> 00:05:58,460
I just had to get that dog

107
00:05:58,460 --> 00:06:02,560
But ever since I brought it home

108
00:06:02,560 --> 00:06:05,259
I've been lying awake all night

109
00:06:05,259 --> 00:06:06,439
I was wrong

110
00:06:06,439 --> 00:06:08,759
I let down my mom and that old lady

111
00:06:08,759 --> 00:06:11,560
Then why did the fire break out here?

112
00:06:14,560 --> 00:06:17,720
Because I didn't sleep at all last night

113
00:06:17,720 --> 00:06:20,600
By this afternoon I was so exhausted

114
00:06:20,600 --> 00:06:22,560
I fell asleep on the bed

115
00:06:22,560 --> 00:06:23,879
Half asleep, half awake

116
00:06:23,879 --> 00:06:26,699
That little dog kept barking and tugging at my clothes

117
00:06:26,699 --> 00:06:28,220
I was puzzled

118
00:06:28,220 --> 00:06:30,519
That dog is usually so quiet

119
00:06:30,519 --> 00:06:32,439
But this time it was barking for no reason

120
00:06:32,439 --> 00:06:33,620
Suddenly

121
00:06:33,620 --> 00:06:35,899
I smelled a strong gas leak

122
00:06:35,899 --> 00:06:38,000
And remembered I forgot to turn off the gas

123
00:06:38,000 --> 00:06:39,920
I panicked and ran outside

124
00:06:39,920 --> 00:06:41,259
Just as I got out the door

125
00:06:41,259 --> 00:06:43,060
The gas tank exploded

126
00:06:43,060 --> 00:06:45,339
It ended up causing a fire.

127
00:06:45,339 --> 00:06:47,599
I'm really useless.

128
00:06:47,599 --> 00:06:49,759
Arrest me.

129
00:06:49,759 --> 00:06:55,060
Why is the auntie drawing blood from the little dog?

130
00:06:55,060 --> 00:06:57,279
Shouldn't it get a transfusion if it's hurt?

131
00:06:57,279 --> 00:06:58,560
This is for a test, kid. You wouldn't understand.

132
00:06:58,560 --> 00:07:05,680
How's the little dog?

133
00:07:05,680 --> 00:07:07,819
They're drawing blood now.

134
00:07:07,819 --> 00:07:08,839
Drawing blood?

135
00:07:11,259 --> 00:07:14,259
Alright, finally done.

136
00:07:14,259 --> 00:07:17,259
Ma'am, you look kind of familiar?

137
00:07:20,259 --> 00:07:23,259
Oh~ Maybe I look like a movie star.

138
00:07:36,259 --> 00:07:39,259
So you like peach juice too.

139
00:07:39,259 --> 00:07:40,180
Detective Chen.

140
00:07:40,180 --> 00:07:41,719
What's up?

141
00:07:41,719 --> 00:07:45,480
Don't you think this fire's origin is a bit strange?

142
00:07:45,480 --> 00:07:46,480
You're right.

143
00:07:46,480 --> 00:07:48,980
It really is too coincidental.

144
00:07:48,980 --> 00:07:52,839
I don't think this is that simple.

145
00:07:52,839 --> 00:07:54,360
Exactly.

146
00:07:54,360 --> 00:07:57,259
And you... aren't that simple either.

147
00:07:58,019 --> 00:08:01,759
Peach~ Peach~

148
00:08:01,759 --> 00:08:02,819
Come chase me!

149
00:08:09,259 --> 00:08:10,259
Hehehehe.

150
00:08:16,259 --> 00:08:20,259
Hehehehe.

151
00:08:32,259 --> 00:08:33,259
Ladies and gentlemen

152
00:08:33,259 --> 00:08:38,259
We now announce the lucky dog who won first place in the first National Beautiful Dog Contest —

153
00:08:38,259 --> 00:08:48,980
Number 153

154
00:08:48,980 --> 00:08:50,179
Early morning

155
00:08:50,179 --> 00:08:55,259
A purebred German dog

156
00:09:03,259 --> 00:09:04,500
Unfair!

157
00:09:04,500 --> 00:09:06,500
Lousy contest

158
00:09:06,500 --> 00:09:08,500
Stupid judges, lousy TV

159
00:09:08,500 --> 00:09:10,500
Bad uncle!

160
00:09:11,500 --> 00:09:12,500
Jingjing, Little Kitten

161
00:09:12,500 --> 00:09:13,500
Oh no

162
00:09:13,500 --> 00:09:14,500
It's Peach

163
00:09:14,500 --> 00:09:15,500
For us

164
00:09:15,500 --> 00:09:17,500
She'll always be number one

165
00:09:18,500 --> 00:09:22,500
I want juice!

166
00:09:22,500 --> 00:09:23,500
Okay

167
00:09:23,500 --> 00:09:24,500
Coming right up, coming right up, coming right up

168
00:09:24,500 --> 00:09:29,500
Next up is the Brave Guardian Award, added by our committee on the spot

169
00:09:29,500 --> 00:09:34,500
We're giving this award to Number 91, Little Kitten

170
00:09:34,500 --> 00:09:37,500
In recognition of her brave rescue of a person during a fire

171
00:09:38,500 --> 00:09:40,500
Victory!

172
00:10:04,500 --> 00:10:07,899
[Ending Theme Music - Full translation available in Ep. 1]

173
00:10:07,899 --> 00:10:12,360
There will always be some unhappiness

174
00:10:12,360 --> 00:10:15,480
Saying goodbye to today

175
00:10:15,480 --> 00:10:19,879
Always makes one feel lost

176
00:10:19,879 --> 00:10:23,320
Look ahead to tomorrow

177
00:10:23,320 --> 00:10:27,620
Waving to me from the horizon

178
00:10:27,620 --> 00:10:31,340
Every day in sunrise and sunset

179
00:10:31,340 --> 00:10:35,340
Spinning into a world of more fantasies

180
00:10:35,340 --> 00:10:40,379
Expecting every second, every moment of life

181
